        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2022-02-08T23:30:42Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Stop Shielding Culpable Platforms Act</b></p> <p> This bill modifies provisions relating to the liability of a provider or user of an interactive computer service (e.g., a social media company) for material placed on its platform by another information content provider.</p> <p>Under current law, a provider or user of an interactive computer service is not considered the publisher or speaker of any information provided by another information content provider. The bill specifies that a provider or user of an interactive computer service may still be treated as a distributor of such information. </p> </p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
